    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ 350\u00b0F/ Gas 4</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with\u00a01 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways and wash carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Slice the<strong> leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely, discarding the tough tops, outer leaves and root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>bacon</strong> is crisp, add the<strong>\u00a0sliced leek</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 2 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock cube</strong>\u00a0in 550ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L]\u00a0</span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir the<strong> stock</strong> into the rice\u00a0and season with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>rice mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven\u00a0for 20 min or until the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked</strong> <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely</p><p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onions</strong>\u00a0finely</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>baked</strong> <strong>risotto</strong> is ready, remove it from the oven</p><p>Stir in the<strong> sugar snap peas</strong> and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Return to the oven for 5 min to warm through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-sugar-snap-and-bacon-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve\u00a0the <strong>baked risotto</strong> in bowls with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, season generously with <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
